        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_InsertDocumentEndOfMonth",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to manage documents related to the end of a billing period within a content management system. It performs two main actions: it first deletes any existing document records for a specific user, billing period, and document name, and then inserts a new document record with the provided details. This ensures that there is only one document per user, billing period, and document name combination."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves basic SQL operations such as DELETE and INSERT, but it also includes handling of unique identifiers and output parameters, which adds a moderate level of complexity. The use of custom data types and the need to manage binary data (documents) further contribute to its complexity."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
